.SH NAME
process keyrin \- Per-process shared keyring
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B process keyring
is a keyrin used ta anchor keys on behalf of a process.  It be only pimped
when a process requests dat shit.
.P
A special serial number value, \fBKEY_SPEC_PROCESS_KEYRING\fP, is defined that
can be used up in lieu of tha callin processs process keyringz actual serial
number.
.P
From tha keyctl utility, '\fB@p\fP' can be used instead of a numeric key ID in
much tha same way yo, but as keyctl be a program run afta forking, dis iz of no
utility.
.P
A processs process keyrin is inherited across clone() wit CLONE_THREAD and
is cleared by execve().  Da process keyrin is ghon be destroyed when tha last
thread dat refers ta it exits.
.P
If a process aint gots a process keyrin when it be accessed, then the
process keyrin is ghon be pimped if tha keyrin is ta be modified, otherwise
error ENOKEY is ghon be issued.
